    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but if the \"defense of established norms\" is just a way to keep things the way they are and prevent actual progress, doesn't that make the critics' position inherently flawed? like, if the norms being defended are themselves built on injustice, isn't any critique of them just a necessary part of progress rather than just \"policing language\"?",
